---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
import SubscribeCard from '../components/SubscribeCard.astro'

const elsewhere = [
  { label: 'GitHub', href: 'https://github.com/MASK-VIII' },
  { label: 'Email', href: 'mailto:contact@enterthelimelight.com' },
] as const
---

<Base
  title="About — Enter the Limelight"
  description="A founder's note from Steven Spacek Jr. — why Limelight exists, why Inkwell, and what comes next."
>
  <main>
    <article class="about">
      <header class="about-head container">
        <p class="eyebrow">A founder's note</p>
        <h1 class="display about-title">Why I'm building Limelight.</h1>
      </header>

      <section class="about-body container">
        <aside class="about-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="about-portrait-frame">
            <div class="about-portrait-tile">
              <span class="about-portrait-initials">SS</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="about-portrait-cap">Steven Spacek Jr.</p>
          <p class="about-portrait-role">Founder, Limelight</p>
        </aside>

        <div class="about-prose">
          <p>
            Inkwell is the writing app I wish I'd had when I was just starting
            out as an author. I had stories I cared about, a few half-good
            chapters, and a folder full of files that wouldn't sit still. Every
            tool I tried had been built for someone further down the road — for
            the writer with a system, a process, a publisher. Not the one
            staring at chapter one wondering whether it should even exist.
          </p>
          <p>
            So I'm making the tool I needed then, and the tool I still need
            now. <a href="/inkwell">Inkwell</a> treats your manuscript like a
            manuscript. It's chapter-first, it works offline, it doesn't ask
            you to sign up before you can start. When you're ready, it produces
            a print-ready PDF and an EPUB you can actually publish.
          </p>
          <p>
            Limelight is the studio around it. It's a small thing — mostly me,
            a handful of writers I trust, and an ambition to keep showing up.
            I want to build the clear software choice for authors just
            starting out, and a serious option for the ones who never quite
            stopped writing. I want to do it in public, in the
            <a href="/journal">journal</a>, with my work on the table.
          </p>
          <p>
            If that sounds like your kind of place, the curtain is up. Pull up
            a seat.
          </p>
          <p class="about-sign">— Steven</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="about-elsewhere container">
        <p class="eyebrow">Elsewhere</p>
        <ul class="about-elsewhere-list">
          {
            elsewhere.map((item) => (
              <li>
                <a href={item.href} rel="me noopener" target="_blank">
                  {item.label}
                </a>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider-rule" />

      <section class="container">
        <SubscribeCard
          eyebrow="Stay close to the work"
          heading="The journal, by email"
          blurb="Letters on craft, the build of Inkwell, and the books I'm betting on. Free, occasional, easy to leave."
        />
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem) 0 1rem;
  }

  .about-head {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
  }

  .about-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 3.75rem);
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-body {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
  }

  @media (min-width: 760px) {
    .about-body {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(12rem, 14rem) 1fr;
    }
  }

  .about-portrait {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-portrait-frame {
    width: 11rem;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    margin: 0 auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gold-dim);
    border-radius: 50%;
    padding: 0.5rem;
    background: var(--color-stage-elevated);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-stage), 0 0 24px rgba(160, 27, 42, 0.2);
  }

  .about-portrait-tile {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: radial-gradient(
      circle at 50% 35%,
      rgba(198, 49, 70, 0.7),
      rgba(110, 15, 26, 0.85) 60%,
      rgba(13, 10, 9, 0.95)
    );
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .about-portrait-initials {
    text-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(255, 230, 180, 0.45);
  }

  .about-portrait-cap {
    margin: 0.85rem 0 0.15rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .about-portrait-role {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .about-prose {
    max-width: var(--prose-max);
    color: var(--color-cream);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .about-prose p {
    margin: 0 0 1.15rem;
  }

  .about-sign {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-gold-bright);
  }

  .about-elsewhere {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-elsewhere-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-elsewhere-list a {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.55rem 1.25rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gold-dim);
    border-radius: 9999px;
    color: var(--color-gold-bright);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  .about-elsewhere-list a:hover,
  .about-elsewhere-list a:focus-visible {
    color: var(--color-cream);
    border-color: var(--color-gold);
    background: rgba(201, 168, 106, 0.08);
  }
</style>
